## 0.1.0
  * Initial scaffold. `clojure-security` skill with vulnerability-class
    reference for Clojure / ClojureScript codebases: read-string / EDN
    reader exploits, Java deserialization sinks, dynamic code execution,
    JVM CVE inheritance (Log4Shell-class), XML / YAML parsing, SQL
    injection via string concatenation, Hiccup / Selmer template
    injection, CLJS XSS surfaces, atom check-then-act races, reflection
    in security-sensitive paths, spec / Malli data leaks in error
    responses, and macros consuming runtime user input. Includes
    grep/Semgrep starter patterns, false-positive heuristics, severity
    triage, investigation order, and tool-finding interpretation
    (clj-kondo, clj-holmes, nvd-clojure, gitleaks, Semgrep).
  * `/security-audit` slash command. Scope arg: `all` (default),
    `staged`, `diff`, or a path. Runs the skill's quick-wins pattern
    sweep, invokes installed tools best-effort (clj-kondo, clj-holmes,
    gitleaks, nvd-clojure, semgrep), triages each finding through the
    skill's investigation order, and produces a structured report
    grouped by severity. Surfaces findings only — never auto-fixes.
  * `PostToolUse` hook on Edit / Write / MultiEdit for
    `.clj`/`.cljs`/`.cljc`/`.edn`/`.bb` files. Runs `clj-kondo` against
    the edited file(s) only. Sub-second (~20ms on a small file). Exit
    semantics: 0 silent on clean / non-Clojure / missing tools; 1 for
    warning-only findings (non-blocking); 2 for error-level findings
    (Claude must address before continuing). Degrades to silent no-op
    if `clj-kondo` or `jq` is not installed. Bash-3.2 compatible
    (macOS default). Iteration target: cleancoders `poker` repo.
  * `SessionStart` hook records the HEAD SHA into
    `.claude/.security-session-start-sha` so the Stop hook has a stable
    diff base on default branches. `SessionEnd` hook removes the marker.
    Both no-op if the cwd is not a git repo.
  * `Stop` hook runs `clj-holmes` (Clojure SAST patterns) and `gitleaks`
    (secret scanning) against the session diff. Diff scope tiered:
    (1) feature branch — merge-base with `origin/<default>`, plus
    uncommitted + untracked; (2) default branch with marker —
    `marker..HEAD` + uncommitted + untracked; (3) no marker — uncommitted
    + untracked only; (4) not a git repo — skip. Exit 0 silent on
    clean / no diff / missing tools / not git; exit 2 blocks the Stop
    and surfaces a structured findings report on stderr so Claude must
    address findings before the turn can end. Reentrancy (`stop_hook_active`)
    re-blocks with an explicit notice — override escalates to the human.
    Findings layout: gitleaks first (secrets are highest-impact), then
    clj-holmes; both link back to the `clojure-security` skill's
    investigation order.
